Syntax: poison:nightshade

Applies nightshade poison to your currently wielded weapon. Nightshade is
a potent plant-derived poison with powerful debilitating effects. It is
one of three weapon poisons available to rogue-line characters (Cipher,
Assassin, Warlock, Nightblade).

Nightshade's debuffing effects can significantly weaken a target, making
it valuable for reducing enemy combat effectiveness before or during a
fight.

Restrictions:
  - Requires a weapon to be wielded.
  - Must have the skill learned.

See also: shelp poison:nightshade poison:arsenic poison:quinine poison weapon backstab
